WEBVTT

00:06:27.101 --> 00:06:30.340
But civil discourse also needs rules,
it needs boundaries.

00:06:31.869 --> 00:06:34.139
For instance, there's a difference

00:06:34.163 --> 00:06:37.504
between language
that is simply rude or demeaning,

00:06:37.528 --> 00:06:41.093
and speech that invokes
hatred and intolerance.

00:06:41.117 --> 00:06:43.029
And specifically of groups.

00:06:43.053 --> 00:06:45.156
And I'm thinking
of racial and ethnic groups,

00:06:45.180 --> 00:06:47.379
I'm thinking of the LGBTQ community,

00:06:47.403 --> 00:06:49.180
I'm thinking of the disabled.

00:06:50.523 --> 00:06:53.684
We snowflakes
call this speech "hate speech."

00:06:54.318 --> 00:06:56.968
And hate speech can lead to violence.

00:06:59.048 --> 00:07:02.713
So, to that point, in the fall of 2018,